Package com.cafean.jobstream.server.components

Class AbstractFileHandle

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.cafean.jobstream.server.components.AbstractFileHandle
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    InputFileHandle, OutputFileHandle
    public abstract class AbstractFileHandle
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    File Handles are used to encapsulate input and output file references by both the Stream Manager and the Execution Wrapper. These classes make use of the common FileReference abstract class for accessor selection and URI creation. They also use JSFileAccessor objects loaded at runtime for low level file manipulation and transmission.
    See Also:
    InputFileHandle, OutputFileHandle

      • setKeywordValue

        public boolean setKeywordValue​(java.lang.String name,
                               java.lang.String value)
        Sets the given keyword to the given value for this file handle. This will replace an existing keyword or add the name/value pair as a new keyword.
        Parameters:
        name - a String containing the name of the keyword
        value - a String containing the new value of the keyword or null if this keyword does not have a value.
